.TH "batadv_forw_packet_bcast_queue" 9 "batadv_forw_packet_bcast_queue" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_forw_packet_bcast_queue \- try to queue a broadcast packet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" batadv_forw_packet_bcast_queue
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_forw_packet *forw_packet "  ","
.BI "unsigned long send_time "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "forw_packet" 12
the forwarding packet to queue
.IP "send_time" 12
timestamp (jiffies) when the packet is to be sent
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function tries to (re)queue a broadcast packet.

Caller needs to ensure that forw_packet->delayed_work was initialized.
